---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Lucy Conklin is a science illustrator and educator based in California, specializing in natural history and scientific illustration.">
  <article class="about">
    <div class="about-container">
      <div class="about-image">
        <img
          src="/images/conklin_bio.jpg"
          alt="Lucy Conklin"
          width="400"
          height="500"
          loading="eager"
        />
        <p class="photo-credit">Photo: Anna Howard Studios</p>
      </div>

      <div class="about-content">
        <h1>About</h1>

        <p>
          As the child of two biologists, I became interested early in how living things are constructed. 
          Backyard dissections felt like a normal part of growing up.
        </p>

        <p>
          I earned a degree in Physics before moving to New York City. After some time there,
          I relocated to California to pursue science illustration formally, completing the
          Science Illustration Certificate Program at California State University, Monterey Bay.
        </p>

        <p>
          Over the years, I have taught science illustration at California State University,
          Monterey Bay and the University of California, Santa Cruz. My freelance clients have
          included the Exploratorium, Edible Magazine, Graze Magazine, Denver Museum of Nature &
          Science, WIRED Magazine, and the Natural Resources Defense Council.
        </p>

        <p>
          A lifelong rider, horses have always held a special place in my work. Of all the subjects
          I draw, I love drawing horses most of all.
        </p>

        <p>
          Today, my studio practice continues to explore the natural world through drawing and
          painting, informed by a background in science, engineering, and careful attention.
        </p>

        <div class="about-contact">
          <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
          <p>
            For commissions and inquiries, please visit my
            <a href="https://www.etsy.com/shop/LucyConklinArt" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Etsy store</a>
            or follow me on Instagram for updates.
          </p>
          <ul class="social-links">
            <li>
              <a href="https://instagram.com/lucyconklin" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                Instagram: @lucyconklin
              </a>
            </li>
            <li>
              <a href="https://pinterest.com/lucyconklin" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
                Pinterest: @lucyconklin
              </a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about {
    padding: 3rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .about-container {
    max-width: 900px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    gap: 3rem;
  }

  @media (min-width: 768px) {
    .about-container {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1.5fr;
      align-items: start;
    }
  }

  .about-image {
    text-align: center;
  }

  .about-image img {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 400px;
    height: auto;
    border-radius: 4px;
  }

  .photo-credit {
    font-size: 0.8rem;
    color: #999;
    margin-top: 0.5rem;
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .about-content h1 {
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    font-size: 2rem;
  }

  .about-content p {
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
    color: #444;
  }

  .about-contact {
    margin-top: 2rem;
    padding-top: 2rem;
    border-top: 1px solid #eee;
  }

  .about-contact h2 {
    font-size: 1.25rem;
    margin-bottom: 1rem;
  }

  .about-contact a {
    color: #333;
    transition: color 0.2s;
  }

  .about-contact a:hover {
    color: #333;
  }

  .social-links {
    list-style: none;
    padding: 0;
    margin-top: 1rem;
  }

  .social-links li {
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .social-links a {
    font-size: 0.9rem;
  }
</style>
